IBM Case Studies













Solution:
IBM Cloud

Industry:
Retail








1-800-FLOWERS.COM Inc.
Anticipating seamless service delivery and reduced costs with an IBM Cloud solution
To integrate its diverse array of order management systems, 1-800-FLOWERS.COM Inc. will migrate to an IBM Commerce on Cloud platform running in an IBM® Bluemix® cloud environment. The retailer anticipates seamless service delivery across brands, greater efficiency, reduced costs and enhanced scalability with the IBM Cloud solution.







Share this

Visit us on Facebook
Visit us on Twitter
Visit us on Google Plus
Visit us on Google Plus


























Business challenge
After years of brand acquisitions, 1-800-FLOWERS.COM Inc. worked with a diverse array of order management systems. To integrate fulfillment processes, the retailer sought a powerful cloud-based solution.


Transformation
IBM will lead a substantial migration project for the retailer, moving 10 major brands to an IBM Commerce on Cloud platform running in  an IBM Bluemix environment.








Results 





 Seamless service delivery
																expected across all company brands and offerings
                                                            

 Efficiency boost and cost cut
																anticipated with an integrated order management system that will streamline fulfillment processes
                                                            

 Greater scalability
																offered to support faster, easier expansion as the business continues to grow
                                                            













Business challenge story
Using a diverse set of order management systems 
After years of expanding its business and acquiring other leading online retail brands, 1-800-FLOWERS.COM was working with a diverse array of order management systems. “When you grow through acquisition, you often adopt homegrown tools from the acquired brands,” says Leslie Leifer, vice president of e-commerce and product development at 1-800-FLOWERS.COM. “Part of the natural growth cycle is eventually building something that can be more easily leveraged for the future.”








“The IBM Cloud solution will establish one high-performance platform that supports the needs of all our brands.”
—Leslie Leifer, Vice President of E-Commerce and Product Development, 1-800-FLOWERS.COM Inc.
                                                            







To consolidate order fulfillment processes on one integrated platform, 1-800-FLOWERS.COM sought a cloud-based solution. “We’re always looking for new technologies to enhance our business,” says Leifer. “Cloud is the cutting-edge tool we need to create opportunities and grow in the future.”














Transformation story
Moving to an IBM Commerce on Cloud platform
Evaluating several leading cloud providers, 1-800-FLOWERS.COM chose an IBM Cloud solution. “It’s important for us to work with a company that can be our partner and isn’t just a vendor,” says Leifer. “IBM has been that for us historically, and we look for it to be that in the future.”
IBM will lead 1-800-FLOWERS.COM’s substantial migration project, moving the retailer’s 10 major brands to an IBM Commerce on Cloud platform running in an IBM Bluemix  cloud environment. “It’s an immense effort,” says Leifer. “But the IBM Cloud solution will establish one high-performance platform that supports the needs of all our brands.”
















Results story
Streamlining service and boosting efficiency
With the Commerce on Cloud solution, 1-800-FLOWERS.COM looks forward to delivering a seamless service experience across brands, boosting efficiency and driving down costs. “Our service teams do a lot of heavy lifting so that each customer has a great experience, regardless of how many systems are involved,” says Leifer. “Soon they’ll be able to provide that experience more quickly and easily.”
Plus, by moving to an integrated cloud-based order management system, 1-800-FLOWERS.COM will be well-positioned to scale operations as business demands. “IBM Cloud is going to make it much easier for us to expand as necessary,” says Leifer.



















About 1-800-FLOWERS.COM Inc.
1-800-FLOWERS.COM Inc. blog
Founded in 1976 and headquartered in Long Island, New York, in the US, 1-800-FLOWERS.COM Inc. is one of the world’s most popular online gift retailers. The company’s offerings include flowers, plants, gift baskets, gourmet foods, confections, candles, balloons and stuffed animals.










Solution components


IBM® Bluemix®
IBM Commerce on Cloud









